Label: CD34
Comment: CD34(+) cell present in the endometrium or decidua

Label: GM-CSF
Comment: Supports trophoblast growth and vascular remodeling enhancing placentation</br>Transcriptome profiling via microarray

Label: IFN-γ
Comment: Robustly produced following activating KIR engagement. </br>IFN-γ inhibits trophoblast invasion by inducing apoptosis and suppressing protease activity</br>Transcriptome profiling via microarray

Label: TNF-α
Comment: Via its action on endometrial stromal cells, TNF-α can also indirectly promote trophoblast invasion by creating a supportive inflammatory environment</br>Elevated TNF-α impairs trophoblast migration and invasion</br>This duality highlights the importance of tightly regulated TNF-α signaling for successful implantation and placental development

Label: IFN-γ
Comment: Robustly produced following activating KIR engagement; critical for immune modulation and trophoblast invasion
